      "content_html": "<a href=\"https://boingboing.net/2026/07/02/nixon-gave-cyprus-a-piece-of-the-moon-then-a-coup-made-it-disappear.html\" rel=\"nofollow\" title=\"Nixon gave Cyprus a piece of the moon. Then a coup made it disappear.\"><img alt=\"Ernie T. Wright./SVS/NASA\" class=\"webfeedsFeaturedVisual wp-post-image\" height=\"653\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/boingboing.net/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/03-lunar-canoyons-image-two.webp?fit=1160%2C653&amp;quality=55&amp;ssl=1\" style=\"display: block; margin: auto; margin-bottom: 5px;\" width=\"1160\" /></a><p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">After Apollo 11, Richard Nixon had NASA make <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cyprus_lunar_sample_displays\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" target=\"_blank\">250 commemorative plaques</a>, each holding about four rice-sized specks of moon dust mounted next to a flag that had flown to the moon and back. In 1970, one went to Cyprus, along with all 135 other countries, all 50 US states, and the UN. &#8212; <a class=\"read-more\" href=\"https://boingboing.net/2026/07/02/nixon-gave-cyprus-a-piece-of-the-moon-then-a-coup-made-it-disappear.html\">Read the rest </a></p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://boingboing.net/2026/07/02/nixon-gave-cyprus-a-piece-of-the-moon-then-a-coup-made-it-disappear.html\">Nixon gave Cyprus a piece of the moon. Then a coup made it disappear.</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://boingboing.net\">Boing Boing</a>.</p>",
